node.text: I don’t think there should be a straight pride OR a gay pride. You shouldn’t celebrate something you were born with and that the majority of Americans accept
I hope this post opens the eyes of some of my fellow straight friends. Realize that you are privileged to be able to go out of your house without fear of being harmed solely based on your sexuality

On top of all this shame, we now have 7 year Olds wearing high heels and bring praised for it. I am being marginalized by trans children now?. Pride parade more like sexual preference parade girl.

I'm gay and I find pride parades to be all about sex and does not represent me at all. I am humble and don't flaunt my sexulaity to strangers. It's a damn shame. If you feel the same you are not alone.
It’s a celebration of sexual identity? No ones saying we’re oppressed. I thought the gay pride was all about expression?
i agree, the only thing i actually have a response to is that yes, we aren’t called sinners but we’re called breeders. but i 110% agree with this post

@headstone.1984 okay, but pride month is 90% to raise awareness for lgbt people. Its not just about partying and being proud. We dont have to raise awareness for straight people as far as im concerned

@peanipple_ I agree, however we shouldn’t wish to abolish straight pride just because it is less important than gay pride. Straight pride and gay pride can still exist in harmony, gay pride can have a month partly dedicated to it (as it is more important), and straight pride doesn’t need a month but can just exist. I don’t see why one could dislike this viewpoint.

@headstone.1984 well because, originally, this whole thing started with 3 homophobic straight dudes, so thats why everyones against it. I understand what you’re trying to say but at this point, every single tweet I’ve seen about straight pride has been homophobic. Now, a day or a week where EVERYONE lgbt AND cis/straight people celebrate together their sexuality as a symbolic of peace, that would be totally awesome. But the way straight pride started was horrible and if we agree with them than we aren’t fighting for our rights. I mean, for example: you wanna buy this cool rope, but the man who designed it and owns the company, is a rapist, killer and he used that exact rope design on his victims. Would you still buy it and support the creator? Or would you find an alternative?
My point is, those 3 men that started straight pride are the creators of the disgusting rope. Instead of just buying that rope, why dont you find an alternative that wont promote homophobia and that everyone can celebrate together?

I’m gay myself, but I still don’t agree with a lot of the hate against straight pride. The concept of straight pride is simply being proud of your sexual orientation, isn’t it hypocritical to support gay pride and not straight pride? But in reference to your post:

1. No, but that doesn’t mean straight pride doesn’t need to exist just because straight people are lying dead in the streets. Straight people still get hate from the LGBT community, all be it to a less dramatic extent, they still deserve the right to express their pride.

2. The title is phrased weirdly; I don’t travel in fear because I am gay. But I get your point, which is why gay activism is much more important than straight activism, but we shouldn’t abolish straight pride completely just because it is a less prominent issue.

3. And now more and more gay marriage is becoming legal. Stopping straight pride isn’t gonna make more places accept gay marriage, in fact it will probably do the adverse effect.

4. Basically the same as 3, gay people are becoming accepted more widely, and hating on straight pride won’t speed up this process.

5. Religion is goddamn stupid, ‘nuff said.
@just_star_stuff I’m not brushing it off saying it’s not a right I’m just refuting the fact that so many people always say marriage is everyone’s right. Its not a right. Not for anyone.
@jb_stays_lit but for straight people it has been basically equivalent to a right. Now the LGBT+ community just wants to be given the same rights.
@just_star_stuff it’s not a right tho 😂 it’s a privilege
I mean marriage isn’t a right tho so
@binana._ 💯💯💯

Heterosexuals get to take pride in their sexuality every damn day so Wtf do they need straight pride for It's just a fucking mockery of gay pride yeah its about expression but they get to express themselves anytime they want without judgement or criticism and what they fail to realize is that gay pride is about allowing those who weren't allowed to express themselves finally be who they are I swear some people just want to be included so damn bad do they not realize how fucking insensitive they are being it's like that one shy kid that's always in the back finally gets to shine but then the golden child steps in to steal their limelight as if they aren't already glorified enough
gay pride month is so unnecessary. the parades are like a clown show and it’s sad. 🤡🤡
